08/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Three Bulgarian companies dealing with arms sales violated the UN weapons embargo imposed on Iraq, according to CIA reports on Iraqi weapons presented earlier this week. 
Local sources Thursday (7 October) identified the three firms as Elmet, Jeff and Sara-M. 
Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov said investigations should be launched to verify the accusations. 
(Mediapool, Sega, Standart, BTA - 07/10/04)
